WEBVTT

00:03.304 --> 00:06.574
- Professor Trotter?
- Hello?

00:06.640 --> 00:08.942
I'm from the Instituto
de la Ciencia Química.

00:09.009 --> 00:10.778
Did-- Didn't you get our letter?

00:13.481 --> 00:16.350
- You got our letter.
- I did. Yes.

00:16.417 --> 00:20.754
[ Bob ] There's just no way
I can leave the university
on such short notice.

00:20.821 --> 00:22.756
I understand
the notice is short,

00:22.823 --> 00:25.593
but the speaker fell ill,
and we thought of you first.
Well, I'm flattered,

00:25.659 --> 00:27.795
but my commitment must be,
of course, to the university.

00:27.861 --> 00:31.799
I'm asking in the name
of science. Come down for
the lecture. A week. Five days.

00:31.865 --> 00:35.136
If the fee
is insufficient--
No. The fee is lavish.

00:35.203 --> 00:38.206
Please.
Please, then, oblige us.
Five days.

00:38.272 --> 00:40.174
People fall ill
for five days.

00:40.241 --> 00:44.112
People remove themselves
for five days to have--

00:44.178 --> 00:46.147
to have romantic assignations.

00:46.214 --> 00:48.716
Your invitation
is flattering, but--

00:48.782 --> 00:53.154
There's a flight this afternoon.
We could stop by your
apartment on Sutter Street.

00:54.588 --> 00:56.957
We could stop by your apartment
and pick up your passport.

00:57.024 --> 00:59.527
How do you know
where my apartment is?

01:07.067 --> 01:09.337
[ Birds Chirping ]

01:13.907 --> 01:15.809
[ Door Opens ]

01:20.080 --> 01:23.817
[ Speaking Spanish ]

01:27.988 --> 01:29.890
Professor Trotter.
Dr. Trotter.

01:29.957 --> 01:32.326
[ Murmurs, Groans ]

01:35.829 --> 01:37.831
I... need some water.

01:40.033 --> 01:42.436
Why did you do this to me?

01:42.503 --> 01:44.338
We have a rather pressing need
for your services.

01:44.405 --> 01:47.241
We will compensate you
generously and return you
to your home with our thanks.

01:47.308 --> 01:50.244
[ Groans ]
What do you want?

01:50.311 --> 01:52.613
Molecular stratification
in pre-crystaline behavior.

01:55.983 --> 01:57.851
You're gonna kill me,
aren't you?

01:57.918 --> 02:02.356
The family for which I work
has charged me to accomplish
this task quickly.

02:02.423 --> 02:06.627
Believe me,
I don't want to harm you.
I want your help.

02:06.694 --> 02:08.196
What do you want?

02:09.430 --> 02:11.532
Our scientists
have told me that--

02:11.599 --> 02:14.335
[ Coughing ]

02:16.404 --> 02:18.906
Professor Trotter.

02:18.972 --> 02:21.709
Our people tell us that...

02:21.775 --> 02:23.977
the process that
you describe could
aid us in our business.

02:24.044 --> 02:26.146
Our business is drugs.

02:26.214 --> 02:28.616
These drugs,
in your country,
are illegal,

02:28.682 --> 02:31.619
causing us an unfortunate
problem in their distribution.

02:31.685 --> 02:33.554
This chemical process
that you discovered--
No, no.

02:33.621 --> 02:35.856
I haven't discovered
any process.

02:35.923 --> 02:38.025
I've--

02:38.091 --> 02:41.495
I've made some
theoretical observations.
In return for your help,

02:44.632 --> 02:46.400
this is yours.

02:46.467 --> 02:49.237
Holds two million dollars.

02:50.404 --> 02:52.540
Wh-- What do you--
What do you want me to do?

02:52.606 --> 02:55.876
We want you to turn
cocaine into paint.

02:58.246 --> 03:00.514
[ All Shouting ]

03:07.288 --> 03:10.190
[ Shouting In Spanish ]

03:10.258 --> 03:13.661
[ Spanish ]

03:19.267 --> 03:22.370
[ Spanish ]

03:29.142 --> 03:32.546
[ Man Shouting In Spanish ]

03:32.613 --> 03:34.815
[ Spanish ]

03:39.287 --> 03:41.689
[ Groans ]

03:48.762 --> 03:50.831
[ Shouts ]

03:50.898 --> 03:53.334
[ Grunting ]

03:53.401 --> 03:55.703
[ Crowd Cheering ]

03:56.837 --> 03:59.407
[ Screams ]

04:05.245 --> 04:08.382
[ Screams, Groans ]

04:08.449 --> 04:12.119
[ Shouting In Spanish ]

04:12.185 --> 04:14.455
[ Grunting ]

04:21.228 --> 04:24.131
Yeah!
[ All Shouting In Spanish ]

04:24.197 --> 04:26.266
[ Spanish ]

04:27.335 --> 04:29.903
[ Crowd Gasps ]

04:32.105 --> 04:34.274
[ Shouts ]

04:41.815 --> 04:44.752
[ All Shouting ]

04:53.193 --> 04:56.063
[ All Shouting ]

05:14.982 --> 05:16.984
Coffee?

05:17.050 --> 05:19.019
No.

05:20.421 --> 05:22.423
What you want me to do,
I think it's possible.

05:22.490 --> 05:25.025
I'm a theoretical chemist.

05:25.092 --> 05:27.461
To accomplish what you want
would require some men...

05:27.528 --> 05:29.296
with industrial,
practical skills
that I don't have.

05:29.363 --> 05:30.798
All right.
But-- But...

05:30.864 --> 05:33.333
what you ask me to do
is illegal, and I can't--

05:33.401 --> 05:37.805
I can't see a situation
where, after having helped you,
you let me live.

05:37.871 --> 05:42.543
- All right, Professor.
All right.
- For if you let me live, why?

05:42.610 --> 05:45.178
Why would I not inform on you?

05:45.245 --> 05:48.949
We need your help--
Yes. You want me to turn
your cocaine into paint.

05:49.016 --> 05:51.552
Of course it's possible.
I'm sure it's been done.
It has been done.

05:51.619 --> 05:53.687
It has been discovered.

05:55.155 --> 05:58.859
We want to turn
our cocaine into
high polymer aviation paint,

05:58.926 --> 06:01.395
which would withstand
the friction heat
and cold of flight.

06:01.462 --> 06:04.097
We want to paint
our planes with it...

06:04.164 --> 06:07.835
and strip them
at the destination
to recover our product.

06:07.901 --> 06:10.070
Your research indicates
this might be done.

06:12.039 --> 06:14.174
Who could actualize it? Huh?

06:14.241 --> 06:17.077
Scott and Halloran?

06:17.144 --> 06:20.548
You mention them here.
They have worked for you. Could
they actualize the process?

06:20.614 --> 06:22.583
How could I tell
my government I helped you?

06:22.650 --> 06:25.586
I--
You were drugged.
You were threatened.

06:25.653 --> 06:27.721
You cooperate to save
the lives of your friends.

06:27.788 --> 06:31.525
- What friends?
- Your colleagues.

06:31.592 --> 06:33.126
Dr. Scott and Dr. Halloran.

06:36.697 --> 06:39.099
[ Chattering In Spanish ]

07:07.561 --> 07:10.731
Please, Mr. Finley,
I mean you no harm.

07:10.798 --> 07:13.867
[ Crowd Shouting In Distance ]

07:15.335 --> 07:17.571
[ Man Speaks Spanish ]

07:17.638 --> 07:19.640
[ Australian Accent ]
Well, I guess you know my name.

07:19.707 --> 07:22.042
Well, it's on your passport.
[ Chuckles ]

07:22.109 --> 07:24.177
How would you like to make
some real money?

07:26.980 --> 07:30.017
What do you call real money?
Enough to pay your debts,

07:30.083 --> 07:33.987
get you out of here,
back to Australia
and to get you started there.

07:36.557 --> 07:40.160
- Who do I have to kill?
- Your opponent
in your next fight.

07:41.461 --> 07:43.897
Ah, you want me to fight
somebody to death?

07:43.964 --> 07:46.399
People die in the ring
all the time.
That's pretty hard...

07:46.466 --> 07:48.702
to kill a man
with your bare hands, mate.

07:48.769 --> 07:52.606
[ Chuckles ]
No. This fight
will be with knives.

07:52.673 --> 07:55.075
You carry a knife.
I'm sure you know
how to use it.

07:56.577 --> 07:59.813
[ Sighs ]
Want a drink?

08:06.453 --> 08:09.022
I know how to use it.

08:09.089 --> 08:11.058
Other fella
fighting to the death--

08:11.124 --> 08:14.094
I gotta assume he knows
how to use it too.

08:14.161 --> 08:15.696
In addition to which,

08:15.763 --> 08:18.298
even the winner
in a knife fight's
coming away cut.

08:18.365 --> 08:21.068
That is, of course,
why you would be
so handsomely compensated.

08:21.134 --> 08:22.603
Should I win.

08:22.670 --> 08:24.638
That's right.
[ Knife Clicks ]

08:24.705 --> 08:27.575
No, thanks.
You don't want to fight?

08:27.641 --> 08:30.978
I like to keep my blood
inside my body.

08:36.216 --> 08:38.986
How'd you know what name
was on my passport?

08:40.087 --> 08:41.989
We stole it.

08:52.199 --> 08:55.135
So you appreciate
the position.

08:56.637 --> 08:58.471
Where do you want me to fight?

08:58.538 --> 09:02.242
[ Man ]
* Give me your secrets
Bring me a sign *

09:02.309 --> 09:06.213
* Give me a reason
to walk the fire *

09:06.279 --> 09:08.348
* See another dawn *

09:08.415 --> 09:10.784
* Through a daughter's eyes *

09:10.851 --> 09:14.722
* You give me a reason
to walk the fire **

09:19.993 --> 09:23.296
[ Jonas ] Where's Billy?
[ Man ] Oh, Dr. Trotter's
in the conference room.

09:23.363 --> 09:25.398
And when do we address
the conference?
Uh, could you--

09:25.465 --> 09:28.368
We're not staying here, right?
Could you have our bags
sent to the hotel?

09:28.435 --> 09:30.938
You know, I have
some papers in my bag.
Well, get 'em out,

09:31.004 --> 09:33.807
and let's have the bags sent,
and can I get
my jacket pressed?

09:43.583 --> 09:45.686
[ Door Opens ]

09:48.956 --> 09:52.192
[ Door Closes ]
I'm sorry.

09:54.594 --> 09:56.730
[ Bob ]
They said they'd release us
after three months.

09:56.797 --> 10:00.367
Look. I don't care what
they said. Whatever they said,
I'm not helping them.

10:01.568 --> 10:03.637
Billy, are you going to
help them?

10:03.704 --> 10:05.773
What happened to your eye?
[ Man ]
¡Señor!

10:05.839 --> 10:08.809
All right. All right.
Whoever you are,

10:08.876 --> 10:10.878
whatever it is
you think we can do--
[ Bob ] George--

10:10.944 --> 10:15.148
No, no, no. There has to be
some way. We can work
something out. Now look.

10:15.215 --> 10:18.251
Whatever it is
you expect us to do,
or you think we can do--

10:18.318 --> 10:21.188
You know, let's just
start from the beginning.

10:21.254 --> 10:24.992
When our families find
that we haven't come home--

10:27.394 --> 10:30.163
- [ Grunting ]
- [ Jonas ]
No.

10:32.332 --> 10:34.735
[ Groaning ]

10:38.071 --> 10:41.341
Stop! Stop.

10:41.408 --> 10:43.744
[ Groaning, Coughing ]

10:52.652 --> 10:56.089
We need your help.
After you've helped us,

10:56.156 --> 10:58.658
after a while,

10:58.726 --> 11:00.694
you will be released...

11:00.761 --> 11:03.263
with this.

11:03.330 --> 11:06.433
If you do not help us,

11:06.499 --> 11:08.401
you will be killed.

11:16.576 --> 11:18.445
I will help you.

11:25.285 --> 11:28.889
Blane, Grey and Brown
by helo from Jungle 1
for their target.

11:28.956 --> 11:31.992
Gerhardt by Zodiac to be
extracted via the Kingfish.

11:32.059 --> 11:34.061
Dot the i's and cross the t's?

11:34.127 --> 11:36.429
The Kingfish is within
the 200-mile limit.

11:36.496 --> 11:39.566
D.O.D. requests sight of
the signed directive
authorizing the incursion.

11:39.632 --> 11:41.434
Since when?
Just now.

11:41.501 --> 11:44.137
Presidential findings
authorized the mission.

11:44.204 --> 11:48.508
Till they found out about it on
the Hill. And they want to know
why two separate extractions.

11:48.575 --> 11:52.312
Well, if they want to put on the
coveralls, I'll put them in the
assembly line.

11:52.379 --> 11:55.816
You ask those worthless
son of a bitch camera hounds...

11:55.883 --> 11:57.951
if they feel competent
to run my operation.

11:58.018 --> 12:00.687
I tell you what.
I'll put them
in the line of fire,

12:00.754 --> 12:03.256
and I'll throw my coat
over my shoulders,
and I'll whore around...

12:03.323 --> 12:05.793
and feel my constituents' pain,
and I'll run for Congress.

12:07.527 --> 12:11.164
You tell the committee
the helo from Jungle 1...

12:11.231 --> 12:13.466
will not accommodate
the team and both the targets.

12:13.533 --> 12:17.370
To divide the targets
is the most effective way
to deliver what they desire.

12:17.437 --> 12:19.973
CINCLANT?

12:20.040 --> 12:22.109
CINCLANT affirms Kingfish
standing by for the extraction.

12:22.175 --> 12:24.244
They are holding
for a green light.

12:24.311 --> 12:26.346
Holding?
They need a signature
from the committee.

12:26.413 --> 12:28.816
They ain't gonna release a sub
unless I got a signature?

12:28.882 --> 12:31.051
Affirmative.
Scheduled jump-off is when?

12:31.118 --> 12:34.554
- Approximately 32 hours.
- Is there anybody else
that can sign off on this?

12:34.621 --> 12:37.357
- Other two members
of the subcommittee.
- Find me one.

12:40.393 --> 12:43.296
And how the hell did this
get up to the Hill?

12:43.363 --> 12:44.998
Yes.

12:45.065 --> 12:47.801
I need the location of
the members of the subcommittee.

12:47.868 --> 12:51.438
Whoever is available.
Uh-huh.

12:51.504 --> 12:54.007
Yes.

12:54.074 --> 12:55.976
Congressman Vasquez
is in France.

12:56.043 --> 12:57.978
Only one in the country.
Congressman Morton.

12:58.045 --> 13:00.848
Where is he?
D.C.

13:00.914 --> 13:04.717
Find him, pin him down,
G5 wheels up in 20 for D.C.
Roger that.

13:04.784 --> 13:07.387
Nice work.

13:07.454 --> 13:10.057
[ Chattering In Spanish ]

13:10.123 --> 13:14.794
- [ Spanish ]
- [ Spanish ]

13:17.497 --> 13:19.332
[ Growling ]

13:22.669 --> 13:25.072
[ Crowd Shouting ]

13:29.977 --> 13:33.013
[ Both Grunting ]

14:06.947 --> 14:09.116
[ Crowd Shouting ]

14:09.182 --> 14:11.218
[ Shouts In Spanish ]

14:11.284 --> 14:13.386
[ Shouts ]

14:13.453 --> 14:15.222
[ Shouting ]

14:24.064 --> 14:26.967
Why would he die
in a training fight?

14:27.034 --> 14:30.303
Eh? Why'd he fight?

14:30.370 --> 14:33.506
If not, they were
going to shoot him.

14:33.573 --> 14:35.943
Why'd they let us watch
a training fight?

14:36.009 --> 14:37.844
To frighten you.

14:37.911 --> 14:40.780
Why'd you want me
to see it?

14:40.847 --> 14:43.516
To take the scales
from your eyes.

14:43.583 --> 14:45.752
Don't think of this
as a fight for money.

14:45.818 --> 14:47.587
He isn't fighting for money.

14:47.654 --> 14:50.123
He's fighting to kill.

14:50.190 --> 14:52.259
You must fight to kill.

14:53.426 --> 14:55.328
Or he will kill you.

15:14.147 --> 15:16.249
[ Phone Rings ]

15:18.185 --> 15:20.220
Congressman Morton?

15:20.287 --> 15:22.089
Do you have an appointment?
Colonel Ryan.

15:22.155 --> 15:23.923
I believe my staff
notified you.

15:23.991 --> 15:26.726
And this is in reference
to what? Sir. Sir.

15:26.793 --> 15:29.729
Sir, do you have an appointment?
Please, where is
the congressman?

15:29.796 --> 15:33.266
Do you have an appointment?
What's your
job description, son?

15:33.333 --> 15:35.468
Sir, my name
is Jeremy Susemiehl,
Congressman Morton's aide.

15:35.535 --> 15:39.072
Well, Mr. Susemiehl,
I suggest you get
your playbook out,

15:39.139 --> 15:42.175
the one with the striped cover
on it, call Joint Special
Operations Command,

15:42.242 --> 15:45.478
give them my name,
follow their instructions.
Yes, sir.

15:45.545 --> 15:47.414
[ Cell Phone Beeps ]

15:48.948 --> 15:51.051
[ Beeps ]
Ryan.

15:51.118 --> 15:53.753
O.N.I. reports a change
in patrol patterns.

15:53.820 --> 15:56.556
Kingfish advises
advance incursion.

15:56.623 --> 16:00.293
Awaiting release.
They advise international
waters soonest.

16:00.360 --> 16:02.996
Window closes 11:35 Lima.

16:03.063 --> 16:05.432
All right.
Thank you, sir.

16:05.498 --> 16:07.267
Thank you very much.

16:07.334 --> 16:11.304
I beg your pardon. I'm to
extend to you all requested
aid and every courtesy.

16:16.976 --> 16:19.046
He's not picking up.

16:19.112 --> 16:22.082
- Where's your boss?
- Sir, he's--

16:22.149 --> 16:24.117
I believe he's absent
on a personal concern.

16:24.184 --> 16:27.254
You know where he is.
Sir, I do not.

16:27.320 --> 16:30.657
Young fella,
I have men in combat.

16:30.723 --> 16:34.127
All I need's a signature,
but I need it
from your boss.

16:34.194 --> 16:36.596
Now, I ain't leaving you
until I got it.

16:36.663 --> 16:38.531
Where is he?

16:47.006 --> 16:49.209
[ Man ]
Sí, papá.

16:54.147 --> 16:56.149
Stop. Stop. No.

16:56.216 --> 16:58.651
These fumes
are highly flammable.

16:58.718 --> 17:01.454
Okay? All right.

17:01.521 --> 17:03.456
Pigment.

17:04.491 --> 17:07.394
Base.
Cocaine hydrochloride,

17:07.460 --> 17:09.796
soluble in water-- in water.

17:09.862 --> 17:13.633
This paint will dry...
sufficiently to apply
another coat.

17:13.700 --> 17:16.303
It will not completely harden
like regular paint,

17:16.369 --> 17:18.571
or we would not be able
to reclaim it.

17:18.638 --> 17:21.474
In order to apply it
to the outside of the plane,

17:21.541 --> 17:24.144
the paint would have to bond
with the polymer.

17:24.211 --> 17:26.479
We addressed that problem
through the composition
of the catalyst.

17:26.546 --> 17:28.448
Show me...

17:28.515 --> 17:31.418
and you will,
as I have said,
go free with that.

17:31.484 --> 17:33.820
What-- What is the matter
with your friend?

17:41.794 --> 17:44.231
May I have a Bible?
Show us a demonstration,

17:44.297 --> 17:47.267
and believe me,
you will be on your way home.

17:48.268 --> 17:50.170
I know you have to kill us.

17:50.237 --> 17:54.507
My friends know it too.
They know, but they can't
face it. All right?

17:54.574 --> 17:58.511
The key is the preparation
of the surface.

17:58.578 --> 18:01.814
In your case,
the aluminum fuselage,
which we have discussed.

18:03.049 --> 18:06.353
At this point,
we will apply heat,

18:06.419 --> 18:08.521
and it will evaporate
the water.

18:19.599 --> 18:23.170
And the substance here
runs off into
the catchment basin.

18:23.236 --> 18:25.172
It's pure cocaine residue.

18:26.473 --> 18:29.342
I've asked for my Bible.
It's in my suitcase.

18:31.944 --> 18:34.847
Is there any way at all
that I could appeal to you?

18:42.655 --> 18:45.558
I've lived a long life.
I've lived a good life.

18:47.059 --> 18:49.162
And I guess it's just the time.

18:49.229 --> 18:51.764
No. Once you've
accomplished your tasks--

18:51.831 --> 18:55.735
Oh, no, please.
We understand each other.

19:05.445 --> 19:08.181
George.
He's a coward.

19:08.248 --> 19:10.183
He always has been.

19:10.250 --> 19:12.385
Base natural.

19:12.452 --> 19:14.287
Highly toxic,
highly flammable.

19:14.354 --> 19:17.390
The reconstituted cocaine
hydrochloride.

19:17.457 --> 19:19.526
On an 80-foot fuselage,

19:19.592 --> 19:23.263
the paint could yield
300 pounds.

19:23.330 --> 19:25.365
All right.
Let's see it work.

19:28.668 --> 19:30.470
Smoke it.

19:30.537 --> 19:32.605
I--
Smoke the damn thing,

19:32.672 --> 19:34.674
and show me
what you have done.

19:35.808 --> 19:38.578
It's poison, isn't it?

19:38.645 --> 19:41.648
What do you think?
That I am a fool?

19:41.714 --> 19:45.518
Huh? You think that
I am a fool and that
you can toy with me?

19:49.389 --> 19:52.024
Wait. Wait.
[ Groans ]

19:52.091 --> 19:54.160
[ Coughs ]
No.

19:54.227 --> 19:57.196
Wait. Ow!
Sí. Bueno. Bueno.

20:03.403 --> 20:06.339
[ Blows Landing ]
[ Groans ]

20:06.406 --> 20:10.277
I want to see this process
working by tonight,

20:10.343 --> 20:12.545
or you're going to watch
your friend die.

20:20.520 --> 20:22.689
What do you want me to do?

20:28.295 --> 20:31.298
[ Crowd Chattering In Spanish ]

20:35.302 --> 20:38.438
[ All Speaking Spanish ]

20:40.340 --> 20:42.442
[ Spanish ]

20:42.509 --> 20:44.711
Ciao.
[ Beeps ]

20:44.777 --> 20:48.481
There'll be some
extraordinarily large betting
on your fight tonight.

20:48.548 --> 20:50.850
I don't know
how that affects me
one way or the other.

20:50.917 --> 20:54.153
A large bettor
would like to meet you.

20:54.220 --> 20:56.389
Does he want me
to throw the fight?

20:56.456 --> 20:58.725
[ Chuckles ]
No. He's my backer.

20:58.791 --> 21:01.728
He's bet on you.
He would like to look you
in the eyes.

21:03.596 --> 21:06.733
Mate, I want my money...
and my passport.

21:06.799 --> 21:08.735
Of course.
Now.

21:08.801 --> 21:10.303
You understand?

21:10.370 --> 21:12.405
Or I'm not stepping in the ring.

21:12.472 --> 21:14.841
I have to go get them.
Oh, no.

21:14.907 --> 21:17.477
- You got 'em on you now.
- Why would I bother
bringing them with me?

21:17.544 --> 21:19.512
Because you freaking
know I've gotta ask.

21:19.579 --> 21:22.382
What do you think,
I'm stupid?

21:22.449 --> 21:24.283
I win this one,
you say, "Just one more."

21:24.351 --> 21:26.285
This is my only fight.

21:26.353 --> 21:29.989
And you gotta have me
go into that ring,
or it's your ass on the line.

21:30.056 --> 21:35.395
You want me to fight,
my money and my passport now.

21:37.163 --> 21:39.298
All right.

21:45.438 --> 21:48.007
Now get out of here.

21:48.074 --> 21:49.942
Let me think.

21:50.009 --> 21:52.779
- There are my men in the hall.
- I understand.

21:52.845 --> 21:56.215
And there is someone
who wants to meet you.

21:56.282 --> 21:58.385
Leave me alone.

22:06.959 --> 22:09.929
Hi. Miss, I swear
there will be
no repercussions.

22:09.996 --> 22:12.799
This is a matter of national
security. I need to speak
with the congressman.

22:12.865 --> 22:15.034
No one will know
that he or you were here.

22:15.101 --> 22:17.970
The congressman?
You work for Congressman Morton.
He keeps this room. That's fine.

22:18.037 --> 22:21.474
I'm sure you two use it
for legislative business,
but I need him right now.

22:21.541 --> 22:25.144
The congressman
is not in that room.
Sir.

22:25.211 --> 22:27.346
Congressman.

22:28.481 --> 22:30.617
Where's the congressman?
I--

22:30.683 --> 22:33.252
This is the congressman's
bungalow, eh?

22:33.319 --> 22:35.287
Where is he?

22:35.354 --> 22:37.424
He was too tired to stay.

22:44.163 --> 22:46.699
[ Bell Rings ]

22:48.535 --> 22:50.369
Uh, is my daughter
all right?
Ms. Dahl,

22:50.437 --> 22:52.672
we have some questions.

22:52.739 --> 22:54.607
- All right.
- Do you have any guns
in your home?

22:54.674 --> 22:57.510
Guns in our home?
Of course not.

22:57.577 --> 23:00.713
- Does your husband?
- My husband is opposed to guns.

23:00.780 --> 23:02.782
Has someone--
Is-Is someone saying--

23:02.849 --> 23:06.052
Mom, I told them
I read something
about guns in a book.

23:06.118 --> 23:09.789
Your daughter
was associating with a boy
who brought a gun to school.

23:09.856 --> 23:13.192
I said-- I said
the teacher said, "The rifles
that Napoléon used"--

23:13.259 --> 23:16.128
- And I said
they weren't rifles.
- How do you know that?

23:16.195 --> 23:18.998
- They were muskets.
- Are you so interested in guns?

23:19.065 --> 23:21.300
- I read it in a book!
- What was the name of the book?

23:21.367 --> 23:23.470
I don't remember.

23:25.438 --> 23:29.709
Ms. Dahl, your daughter's
been behaving very oddly since
she came to the school.

23:29.776 --> 23:32.278
She seems to have no friends.

23:32.344 --> 23:37.717
Miss Grimes reports that
she has shunned overtures of
friendship from her classmates.

23:37.784 --> 23:42.989
She reports that you are
reclusive, secretive
and, I beg your pardon--

23:43.055 --> 23:45.492
and I assure you that
I intend no disrespect--

23:45.558 --> 23:48.695
I only speak
in your best interest--
furtive.

23:48.761 --> 23:51.097
I'm not. I'm not.
I'm telling the truth.

23:51.163 --> 23:54.266
- Well, why are you
so interested in guns?
- Let me-- Let me--

23:54.333 --> 23:57.737
Uh, just let me explain.
I'm not. I hate them.
And I hate you too.

23:57.804 --> 24:00.306
I don't understand
why you're torturing me.

24:00.372 --> 24:03.643
I wish everybody in
this school would just--
Would just what?

24:03.710 --> 24:06.045
You wish everybody...

24:06.112 --> 24:07.680
in the school would what?

24:09.582 --> 24:11.718
[ Whirring ]

24:11.784 --> 24:14.554
It was about a book report.
I understand.

24:14.621 --> 24:16.589
Well, I didn't do
anything wrong.

24:16.656 --> 24:18.758
- I'm sure you didn't.
- I know you didn't.

24:18.825 --> 24:21.093
Now, just excuse us, okay?

24:21.160 --> 24:23.462
It's all right.
Just wait in the other room.
[ Knocks ]

24:23.530 --> 24:25.498
[ Door Opens ]

24:25.565 --> 24:29.368
- Everything all right?
- Lissy was called out
in school today.

24:29.435 --> 24:30.903
- She was suspended.
- What happened?

24:30.970 --> 24:32.972
They dragged some comment
out of her about guns.

24:33.039 --> 24:35.642
Said she knew
too much about a rifle.
Call our friend,

24:35.708 --> 24:37.610
find out what he has
on the principal.

24:37.677 --> 24:40.379
Tell him the crash code.

24:40.446 --> 24:42.882
The comment
was just a trigger.

24:42.949 --> 24:44.884
- What did the trigger release?
- Their suspicions.

24:44.951 --> 24:47.353
Since she came to the school,
she's been acting strangely.

24:47.419 --> 24:50.422
Consciously
they made allowances--
new student and so on.

24:50.489 --> 24:53.526
- Uh-huh. Yes, I have.
- But deep down inside,
they knew she was wrong.

24:53.593 --> 24:56.963
Last week, she knew
a boy who had a gun.

24:57.029 --> 24:58.931
Now she likes guns,

24:58.998 --> 25:02.669
and she gets up and says,
"I hate you all.
I wish you would die."

25:02.735 --> 25:05.037
- They think
she might be homicidal.
- Well,

25:05.104 --> 25:07.339
from their perspective,
it brings things into focus.

25:07.406 --> 25:10.209
Janet Green, principal.

25:10.276 --> 25:14.080
We're not gonna play the cards.
We're gonna play the players.

25:14.146 --> 25:19.518
School principal, Janet Green,
37 years old, M.A., education,
M.A., psychology.

25:19.586 --> 25:21.988
Divorced twice.
No children.

25:22.054 --> 25:25.491
Two years working for
the church in Nicaragua.

25:25.558 --> 25:27.459
Good woman.
Woman of conscience.

25:27.526 --> 25:30.196
- She only wants to
protect her students.
- [ Molly ] There it is.

25:30.262 --> 25:34.300
There it is.
We can only see
what we can imagine.

25:34.366 --> 25:38.337
Her sister is serving life
for narcotics and murder.

25:38.404 --> 25:43.109
So, she never again
wants to say,
"I knew it all the time."

25:43.175 --> 25:46.278
The last thing in the world
she wants is the first thing
in the world she sees.

25:46.345 --> 25:49.348
- She sees what she fears.
- What does she fear?

25:49.415 --> 25:51.483
Loss of control.

25:51.550 --> 25:55.421
I'm afraid they're gonna
call in their psychiatrist.
How do we stop 'em?

25:55.487 --> 25:57.123
We'll bring our psychiatrist.

25:57.189 --> 25:59.291
- And who would that be?
- That'll be you.

26:18.344 --> 26:20.212
Just--

26:21.480 --> 26:23.582
All right.
Let's see you smoke it.

26:23.650 --> 26:26.318
It's okay. Smoke it.

26:38.064 --> 26:40.366
[ Coughing ]
More, please.

26:45.437 --> 26:47.940
[ Coughs ]

27:01.353 --> 27:04.023
[ Man Laughs ]

27:04.090 --> 27:06.893
We set up the factory tomorrow.

27:21.708 --> 27:23.976
Sí. Sí.

27:34.787 --> 27:38.357
[ Screaming ]

27:43.029 --> 27:46.198
[ Man Speaking Spanish ]

28:06.986 --> 28:09.121
[ No Audible Dialogue ]

28:09.188 --> 28:11.290
[ Spanish ]

28:28.240 --> 28:30.242
[ Chuckles ]

28:32.211 --> 28:34.246
[ Spanish ]

28:37.316 --> 28:40.186
[ Spanish ]

29:04.877 --> 29:06.979
[ Whispering ]

29:10.216 --> 29:11.483
Shh.

29:14.787 --> 29:16.923
Mr. Finley.

29:18.724 --> 29:20.759
So you're the big bettor.

29:20.827 --> 29:24.596
I wanted to look you
in the eyes.

29:24.663 --> 29:26.598
Before you bet on me.

29:26.665 --> 29:28.634
Yes. That's right.

29:28.700 --> 29:31.570
[ Man On P.A. Speaking Spanish ]

29:31.637 --> 29:34.106
They're calling your fight.

29:39.846 --> 29:41.948
[ Cell Phone Rings ]

29:43.382 --> 29:45.284
I need to talk to you.

29:49.055 --> 29:51.023
I need to talk to you, mate.

29:52.658 --> 29:54.726
Okay.

29:54.793 --> 29:56.863
[ Man On P.A. Speaking Spanish ]

30:50.449 --> 30:52.384
[ Grunts ]

30:56.488 --> 30:58.190
What is cover?

30:58.257 --> 31:00.492
Cover is what's true.
What's true?

31:00.559 --> 31:04.630
It is true that
my name is Kate Logan,
that I am a psychologist.

31:04.696 --> 31:07.566
- Where did you get your degree?
- George Washington Univ--

31:07.633 --> 31:10.970
- Did they clear that with--
- They can call the alumni
office. It'll hold.

31:11.037 --> 31:12.871
Because I'm concerned
that-- that they'll ask--

31:12.939 --> 31:16.842
Cover is what's true.
Cover is what's true.

31:16.909 --> 31:18.978
What is true?

31:19.045 --> 31:21.147
Lissy was referred to me
by Dr. Harriet...

31:22.949 --> 31:24.984
Voight.

31:25.051 --> 31:27.053
Lissy is suffering
from a mild--

31:27.119 --> 31:29.989
mild depression
and free-floating anxiety.

31:30.056 --> 31:31.924
Good. Now put it
out of your mind.

31:31.991 --> 31:36.528
Don't obsess on it.
You think on it,
you'll bring it to pass.

31:36.595 --> 31:40.766
Acute but transient anxiety,
worsened by the move--

31:40.832 --> 31:43.202
- Um, the--
- The incident.

31:43.269 --> 31:45.171
The incident.
Right.

31:45.237 --> 31:49.608
You tell them something
private, sexual or shameful,
and they'll look away.

31:50.876 --> 31:52.979
That's right.

31:55.447 --> 31:57.616
Well, off you go.

32:01.553 --> 32:04.523
Ms. Green, I understand
that your responsibility
is to the school.

32:04.590 --> 32:07.093
Okay. One moment.
Now, I've scheduled
a meeting with Lissy...

32:07.159 --> 32:09.428
and our district
school psychologist.

32:09.495 --> 32:11.430
I hope you don't--

32:11.497 --> 32:14.133
I sincerely hope you
will not take offense or--
[ Doorbell Rings ]

32:14.200 --> 32:17.003
No. On the contrary.

32:17.069 --> 32:19.638
Lissy has her own psychologist
I'd like you to meet.

32:21.440 --> 32:24.210
Ms. Green,
this is Dr. Kate Logan.

32:25.177 --> 32:27.346
Ms. Green.
Kate Logan.

32:27.413 --> 32:29.481
I hope you didn't
have to rearrange
your day.

32:29.548 --> 32:32.151
Not at all. Ms. Green,

32:33.752 --> 32:36.522
Lissy has been under my care
since their arrival here.

32:36.588 --> 32:39.091
Uh, you-- you've been
treating Lissy for--

32:39.158 --> 32:41.560
Depression.
And acute anxiety.

32:41.627 --> 32:44.830
What-- Is she dangerous?
No. She is not.

32:44.896 --> 32:48.267
Are you sure?
Because I have to
tell you, uh, Dr.--

32:48.334 --> 32:51.337
Logan.
Dr. Logan. Yes.

32:51.403 --> 32:54.106
- Uh, you said "acute."
- That's right.

32:54.173 --> 32:57.309
Well, do you know
what occasioned it?

32:59.511 --> 33:01.380
Is it necessary?

33:01.447 --> 33:04.883
Uh, it's all right.
It's all right.

33:04.950 --> 33:06.985
Um,

33:07.053 --> 33:09.421
about a year ago,

33:09.488 --> 33:13.992
my daughter was
the victim of a sexual--

33:19.031 --> 33:21.100
[ Rings ]

33:21.167 --> 33:23.802
[ Beeps ]
Hello?

33:23.869 --> 33:26.004
Yes?

33:27.473 --> 33:30.442
George Watson University?

33:30.509 --> 33:34.380
George Washington University
is unsafe.

33:34.446 --> 33:37.116
It wasn't safe.
Why? What?

33:37.183 --> 33:39.017
Wh-What--
What do you mean unsafe?

33:39.085 --> 33:41.220
You cleared it.

33:41.287 --> 33:44.823
I understand. And I will, of
course, guard your confidence.
[ Cell Phone Rings ]

33:44.890 --> 33:46.358
Excuse me.

33:46.425 --> 33:48.527
[ Beeps ]
It's a classical situation.

33:48.594 --> 33:51.630
Patient confidentiality
versus the institutional
need to know.

33:54.100 --> 33:57.536
Oh, what school
did you go to?
George Washington University.

33:57.603 --> 34:00.306
Oh, my first husband went there.
Yeah, when were you there?

34:00.372 --> 34:02.174
[ Cell Phone Rings ]

34:02.241 --> 34:05.411
Come on, Kim!
[ Beeps ]

34:05.477 --> 34:07.479
When were you at G.W.?
I--

34:07.546 --> 34:10.516
When was your husband there?
Well, he taught there.

34:10.582 --> 34:13.952
- [ Ringing Continues ]
- Uh, '81 to '95.
Bill Nelson.

34:14.019 --> 34:16.988
I-- I beg your pardon,
Ms. Green.

34:17.055 --> 34:19.291
[ Beeps ]
A patient.

34:19.358 --> 34:21.827
Yes. Thank you, Dr. Logan,
for your time and coming in.

34:21.893 --> 34:23.929
Well, you-you must have had him.

34:23.995 --> 34:26.832
Bill Nelson.

34:26.898 --> 34:30.068
Kind of small,
retiring fellow,
twinkle in his eye.

34:30.136 --> 34:32.271
Oh. Yes. Bill Nelson.

34:32.338 --> 34:35.507
Uh, lonely, retiring fellow.

34:35.574 --> 34:38.009
Yeah, but he's 6'4".
He's an ex-marine.

34:38.076 --> 34:40.146
And I'm calling the police.

34:43.081 --> 34:45.851
- [ Gasps ]
- Put the phone down. Please put
the phone down, Ms. Green.

34:45.917 --> 34:47.686
Okay. Who are you?

34:47.753 --> 34:50.556
My name is Tamara Tillings.
I'm a federal agent.

34:50.622 --> 34:52.691
All right.
Please show me
your identification.

34:52.758 --> 34:54.560
I don't carry it.
Hello?

34:54.626 --> 34:58.330
I don't carry it,
Ms. Green, because I can't.

34:58.397 --> 35:00.599
What you have discovered,
Ms. Green,

35:00.666 --> 35:04.203
is a cell of the Federal
Witness Protection Agency.

35:04.270 --> 35:07.005
These people are all
under my protection.

35:07.072 --> 35:09.875
So you're with the F.B.I.?
That's right.

35:09.941 --> 35:12.811
You can call
the local office.
They won't have my name.

35:12.878 --> 35:17.783
You can call Washington.
They'll deny
my existence... to you.

35:17.849 --> 35:20.186
- Why to me?
- Ms. Green,

35:20.252 --> 35:23.222
theoretically I shouldn't
even be speaking to you.

35:23.289 --> 35:26.192
- Why?
- Take her out.

35:29.661 --> 35:32.831
Your sister, confined
in a federal penitentiary.

35:32.898 --> 35:36.134
For you, in contact
with a federal prisoner,

35:36.202 --> 35:38.870
to have any knowledge
of our operations here...

35:38.937 --> 35:40.706
is a grave breach
in security,

35:40.772 --> 35:42.508
which my superior
would say...

35:42.574 --> 35:47.145
greatly endangers Ms. Dahl
and her daughter.

35:48.814 --> 35:52.384
Now you tell me.
What am I supposed to do?

35:59.925 --> 36:01.860
[ Man Shouting In Spanish ]

36:06.932 --> 36:08.099
[ Man ]

36:08.166 --> 36:10.769
[ Father ]

36:12.371 --> 36:14.873
[ Door Closes ]
It's the boy's father.

36:14.940 --> 36:17.175
Let's go.

36:21.880 --> 36:23.515
Shh.

36:34.960 --> 36:37.929
Take the shot. Get that
filth out of your system.
You got it, Top.

36:53.845 --> 36:54.846
Guillermo, Fernando--

37:25.110 --> 37:27.012
Night-night.

37:35.321 --> 37:36.855
[ Machine Gun Fire ]

37:46.332 --> 37:48.700
- [ Groans ]
- [ Machine Gun Fire ]

37:50.436 --> 37:52.871
[ Man Groans ]

38:01.647 --> 38:04.082
[ Grey ]
You hit, Top?

38:04.149 --> 38:05.917
It's just a little nick.
I'm fine.

38:11.289 --> 38:13.291
- Looks like he caught one.
- He's dead?

38:13.359 --> 38:15.994
And that will be that.

40:09.508 --> 40:11.610
Thank you for your patriotism.

40:11.677 --> 40:14.780
You can be assured of it.
One other thing.
If anyone--

40:14.846 --> 40:18.049
anyone is over-inquisitive
about Ms. Dahl
and her daughters,

40:19.551 --> 40:22.654
call me.
I will call you.
Thank you.

40:24.222 --> 40:27.893
Ms. Dahl,
I beg your pardon.

40:27.959 --> 40:29.327
It's all right.

40:29.394 --> 40:30.862
Thank you.

40:42.608 --> 40:44.676
How did you
put one over on her?

40:44.743 --> 40:47.813
I told her the secret.
Reminded her
she already knew it.

40:47.879 --> 40:49.314
The secret?

40:49.380 --> 40:51.950
Nothing is what it seems.

40:56.488 --> 40:59.090
[ Crickets Chirping ]

41:01.192 --> 41:03.094
Mrs. Morton.
Yes?

41:03.161 --> 41:05.864
Where is the congressman?
Uh, he's-- he's lying down.
He's resting.

41:05.931 --> 41:07.966
He's just not feeling--
Congressman Morton.

41:08.033 --> 41:10.669
Congressman Morton.

41:10.736 --> 41:13.338
- Yes?
- Thank God, sir.
I need you to sign this.

41:13.404 --> 41:15.440
What is it?

41:15.507 --> 41:19.711
Sir, this is the authorization
for extraction of two narco
terrorists from foreign waters.

41:19.778 --> 41:22.848
Mission named Conduit.
You were briefed in committee.

41:22.914 --> 41:24.516
It's of the utmost
urgency, sir.
Conduit.

41:24.583 --> 41:26.184
Yes, of course.
Thank God.

41:26.251 --> 41:28.754
Further.
[ Mutters ]

41:32.490 --> 41:34.560
Hello. I'm in possession.
Yes.

41:34.626 --> 41:37.563
Negative.
They weren't able to hold,
Colonel.

41:37.629 --> 41:40.498
Navy relates they have, quote,
"Missed the window."

41:40.566 --> 41:44.636
They ran up against
patrol boat schedules,
and they have withdrawn the sub.

41:44.703 --> 41:46.171
The extraction's scrubbed.

41:46.237 --> 41:49.675
Dirt Diver will
have to self-extract
without the package.

41:54.980 --> 41:56.915
I hope this gives you
everything that you require.

41:56.982 --> 41:59.517
I'm deeply sorry
for the disruption.

41:59.585 --> 42:01.219
Anything for our boys.

42:03.421 --> 42:05.591
Thanks for your help, ma'am.

42:09.327 --> 42:11.229
[ Seagulls Squawking ]

42:29.114 --> 42:31.549
[ Dog Barking ]

42:35.420 --> 42:37.322
[ Speaking Spanish ]

42:49.467 --> 42:51.937
[ Seagulls Squawking ]

42:58.844 --> 43:01.012
[ Speaking Spanish ]

43:02.714 --> 43:04.015
[ Gunshots ]

43:14.059 --> 43:16.127
[ Woman Speaking Spanish ]

43:18.897 --> 43:21.132
[ Man Speaking Spanish ]
